    text: "The sun came up over the big green hill. The rooster began to crow loud and long at the top of his voice. The farmer woke up when he heard it and got dressed quickly. He put on his tall boots and his wide brown hat. He went outside into the cool morning air to feed the animals. First he fed the hungry pigs their slop in the muddy pen. Then he threw handfuls of yellow corn to the chickens in the yard. The horse got a big pile of fresh hay and a bucket of clean water. The cow needed to be milked before the day could really begin. The farmer sat down on a small wooden stool next to her. He pulled gently and the warm white milk came flowing out. He filled a large silver bucket almost all the way up. The dog ran around the yard barking at everything it saw. It wanted to stop and play with the farmer right then. But the farmer still had far too much work left to do. He needed to water all the plants growing in the garden. The vegetables needed a great deal of care each and every morning. He carried a heavy metal can filled up with cold water. He poured it slowly around the beans and the tall corn stalks. Then he checked each tomato plant very carefully for bugs. He pulled some weeds that had grown up overnight in the soil. He fixed a part of the fence that had fallen over in the wind. After that he went inside and sat down for a good breakfast. He was tired but very happy with all the work he had done. The farm was in good shape for another busy day.",
